    "reasoning": "We first find the set S of points P such that iterates of f(P) = (x^2 - y^2, 2xy - y^2) converge to (0,0). We discover the invariant quadratic form Q(x,y) = x^2 - xy + y^2, which satisfies Q(f(P)) = Q(P)^2. Thus, convergence occurs if and only if Q(P) < 1, so S is the interior of the ellipse x^2 - xy + y^2 < 1. The area of this ellipse is computed as 2π/√3. Setting this equal to π√r gives √r = 2/√3, so r = 4/3.\n\nNext, Alice writes r + 2999/3 = 4/3 + 2999/3 = 1001 letters, each chosen uniformly from {a,b,c}. The operation of erasing two distinct letters and replacing with the third allows reduction to a single letter if and only if the counts of the three letters are not all odd. For 1001 letters, the probability that all counts are odd is 1/4 - 1/(4·3^{1000}). Thus, the probability that reduction to one letter is possible is 1 minus that, which simplifies to (3^{1001}+1)/(4·3^{1000}).",
